70
00:04:15.940 --> 00:04:19.440
transformation of precancerous lesions in colon to cancer.

71
00:04:20.280 --> 00:04:22.600
Two studies focused on breast cancer.

72
00:04:23.040 --> 00:04:27.020
One used single-cell sequencing, RNA sequencing to profile metastatic cancer

73
00:04:27.080 --> 00:04:30.700
from 60 individuals, while the other described the underlying

74
00:04:30.740 --> 00:04:33.780
genetic networks that define the breast cancer subtypes.

75
00:04:35.820 --> 00:04:39.460
Some of the common themes that came across these tumor types and analysis

76
00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:43.159
include the recurring pattern of cellular spatial

77
00:04:43.960 --> 00:04:47.510
patterns that is indicative of co-evolution of tumor and

78
